HTTP-Enabled Location Delivery (HELD)
2010", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document defines a Layer 7 Location Configuration Protocol (L7 LCP) and describes the use of HTTP and HTTP/TLS as transports for the L7 LCP.  The L7 LCP is used for retrieving location information from a server within an access network.  It includes options for retrieving location information in two forms: by value and by reference.  The protocol is an extensible application-layer protocol that is independent of the session layer. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"]; 

